","format":false,"excerpt":"Maymun ibn Mihran reported: A man came to Salman al-Farisi, may Allah be pleased with him, and he said, \u201cO Abu Abdullah, advise me.\u201d Salman said, \u201cDo not speak.\u201d The man said, \u201cHow can one live among people and not speak?\u201d Salman said, \u201cIf you speak, speak the truth or\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4206,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/05\/duties-allah-selves-family\/","url_meta":{"origin":26216,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Duties: Rights of Allah, your family, and yourself","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Juhayfah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, made a fellowship between Salman and Abu Darda. Salman visited Abu Darda and found his wife Umm Darda dressed in worn-out clothing. He asked her why she was like this. She said, \u201cYour brother Abu Darda is not interested\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11611,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/22\/salman-king-not-a-khalifah\/","url_meta":{"origin":26216,"position":2},"title":"Salman on Khilafah: Unjust leaders are kings, not Caliphs","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 22, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Salman al-Farisi reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said to him, \u201cAm I a king or a Caliph?\u201d Salman said, \u201cIf you acquire as much as two coins from the lands of the Muslims, more or less, then you place it where it does not belong,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21654,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/01\/18\/salman-holy-land-itself\/","url_meta":{"origin":26216,"position":3},"title":"Salman on Holiness: Holy Land itself does not make anyone holy","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 18, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Malik reported: Salman al-Farisi, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, land itself does not make anyone holy. Rather, a human being is only made holy by his righteous deeds.\u201d Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a\u02bc 1500 \u0639\u0646 \u0645\u0627\u0644\u0643 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0633\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0627\u0631\u0633\u064a \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0636\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062a\u064f\u0642\u064e\u062f\u0651\u0650\u0633\u064f \u0623\u064e\u062d\u064e\u062f\u064b\u0627 \u0648\u064e\u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u064a\u064f\u0642\u064e\u062f\u0651\u0650\u0633\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0625\u0650\u0646\u0652\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25534,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/04\/prophet-taught-everything\/","url_meta":{"origin":26216,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Cleanliness: Your Prophet taught you everything!","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 4, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Salman reported: The idolaters said, \u201cIndeed, your companion teaches you everything, even he teaches you how to defecate!\u201d Salman said, \u201cIt is so. The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, prohibited us from removing excrement using the right hand, or while facing the direction of prayer. The Prophet prohibited\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":29137,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/10\/salman-humility-yawm-al-qiyamah\/","url_meta":{"origin":26216,"position":5},"title":"Salman on Humility: Humble yourself for Allah, Allah raises you up","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 10, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Jarir reported: Salman al-Farisi, may Allah be pleased with him, said \u201cO Jarir, be humble for the sake of Allah. Whoever humbles himself for Allah, Allah will raise him up on the Day of Resurrection. O Jarir, do you know what will be darkness on the Day of Resurrection?\u201d I\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/26216","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\